LUTFY v. STARBUCK. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, Second Department. May 10, 1907.) Appeal from Special Term. Action by Deeb Lutfy against Edgar D. Starbuck. From an order denying defendant’s motion for a change of venue, he appeals. Reversed.

Argued before JENKS, HOOKER, GAYNOR, RICH, and MILLER, JJ.

PER CURIAM.

Order reversed, with $10 costs and disbursements, and motion granted, with costs. See Lutfy v. Sullivan (decided herewith) 104 N. Y. Supp. 177.
